    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I don't think there will be a solution to this, since Java can run on non-pc devices. </p>\n\n<p>Most portable devices don't support double-click. </p>\n\n<p>You may keep track of the moment of each mouse click and fire your own \"double-click\" event. But I don't think this is a good idea.</p>\n"
